      "source": [
        "# DIRISA Datathon 2026\n",
        "## Data Visualization Training Notebook\n",
        "\n",
        "**Theme:** Education Student Dataset \u2013 South African Context  \n",
        "**Focus:** Using visualization to answer real questions from data.\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook contains **markdown explanations only**. Code will be added later during the practical session.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Training Goal\n",
        "\n",
        "Data visualization is not only about creating charts.\n",
        "\n",
        "It helps us:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Understand data quickly\n",
        "- Identify patterns\n",
        "- Compare groups\n",
        "- Detect problems\n",
        "- Communicate insights\n",
        "- Support decision-making\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Learning Outcomes\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of this session, participants should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Explain why data visualization is important\n",
        "- Select the correct chart for a question\n",
        "- Interpret charts clearly\n",
        "- Build a visual story from data\n",
        "- Use visualization to support decisions\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Dataset Context\n",
        "\n",
        "We will use a realistic **student education dataset** based on a South African university context.\n",
        "\n",
        "Possible columns:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Student ID\n",
        "- Province\n",
        "- Gender\n",
        "- Faculty\n",
        "- Programme\n",
        "- Campus\n",
        "- Mathematics Mark\n",
        "- Attendance Rate\n",
        "- Study Hours\n",
        "- LMS Logins\n",
        "- Funding Status\n",
        "- Internet Access\n",
        "- GPA\n",
        "- Risk Status\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. South African Provinces\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset will include students from the nine provinces:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Eastern Cape\n",
        "- Free State\n",
        "- Gauteng\n",
        "- KwaZulu-Natal\n",
        "- Limpopo\n",
        "- Mpumalanga\n",
        "- Northern Cape\n",
        "- North West\n",
        "- Western Cape\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. Why Visualization Comes Before Modelling\n",
        "\n",
        "Before building a machine learning model, we must understand the data.\n",
        "\n",
        "Visualization helps us answer:\n",
        "\n",
        "- What does the data look like?\n",
        "- Are there missing values?\n",
        "- Are there outliers?\n",
        "- Are some groups performing better?\n",
        "- Are variables related?\n",
        "- Which features may be useful for modelling?\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. Question 1: Province and Mathematics Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Do students from Gauteng tend to pass Mathematics more than students from other provinces?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Possible Charts:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Bar Chart\n",
        "- Box Plot\n",
        "- Grouped Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Compare Mathematics performance by province.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. Question 2: Highest Average Mathematics Mark\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which province has the highest average Mathematics mark?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Column Chart or Horizontal Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why:**  \n",
        "We are comparing values across categories.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. Question 3: Student Numbers by Province\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which province contributes the highest number of students?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Horizontal Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why:**  \n",
        "It ranks provinces clearly and is easy to read.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 9. Question 4: Attendance and Mathematics\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Does attendance affect Mathematics performance?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Scatter Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "**Variables:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Attendance Rate\n",
        "- Mathematics Mark\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Check whether higher attendance is linked to higher Mathematics marks.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 10. Question 5: Study Hours and Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Do students who study more hours per week perform better in Mathematics?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Scatter Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why:**  \n",
        "Both variables are numerical.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 11. Question 6: Faculty Pass Rate\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which faculty has the highest Mathematics pass rate?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Identify faculties where students are performing well or struggling.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 12. Question 7: Funding Status and Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Are NSFAS-funded students performing differently from self-funded students?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Grouped Bar Chart or Box Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Compare performance between funding groups.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 13. Question 8: Internet Access and Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Do students with internet access perform better than students without internet access?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Grouped Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Explore whether access to digital resources affects performance.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 14. Question 9: At-Risk Students by Campus\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which campus has the highest number of at-risk students?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Stacked Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Identify where academic support may be needed most.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 15. Question 10: Distribution of Mathematics Marks\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "What is the distribution of Mathematics marks?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Histogram\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Understand whether most students are passing, failing, or grouped around certain mark ranges.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 16. Question 11: Outliers in Mathematics Marks\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Are there outliers in Mathematics marks?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Box Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Identify unusually low or high marks.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 17. Question 12: GPA by Province\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "How does GPA differ by province?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Box Plot\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Compare distribution, spread, and variation in GPA across provinces.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 18. Question 13: Variables Related to Performance\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which variables are related to student performance?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Correlation Heatmap\n",
        "\n",
        "**Variables may include:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Attendance Rate\n",
        "- Study Hours\n",
        "- LMS Logins\n",
        "- Mathematics Mark\n",
        "- GPA\n",
        "- Assignment Average\n",
        "- Exam Mark\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 19. Question 14: Largest Programmes\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which programmes have the highest number of students?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Horizontal Bar Chart\n",
        "\n",
        "**Insight Goal:**  \n",
        "Rank programmes by enrolment.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 20. Question 15: Academic Support Dashboard\n",
        "\n",
        "**Question:**  \n",
        "Which student groups may need academic support?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Best Chart:**  \n",
        "Dashboard\n",
        "\n",
        "**Dashboard may include:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Total Students\n",
        "- Average Mathematics Mark\n",
        "- Pass Rate\n",
        "- Students by Province\n",
        "- Attendance vs Mathematics Mark\n",
        "- At-Risk Students by Campus\n",
        "- Risk Status Distribution\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 21. Chart Selection Guide\n",
        "\n",
        "| Question Type | Best Chart |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| Compare categories | Bar Chart |\n",
        "| Show trends over time | Line Chart |\n",
        "| Show proportions | Pie Chart / Donut Chart |\n",
        "| Show distribution | Histogram |\n",
        "| Show relationship between two numbers | Scatter Plot |\n",
        "| Show outliers | Box Plot |\n",
        "| Show correlation between many variables | Heatmap |\n",
        "| Show geographic data | Map |\n",
        "| Combine many insights | Dashboard |\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 22. Data Storytelling Structure\n",
        "\n",
        "When presenting a visualization, explain:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. What question was asked?\n",
        "2. What chart was used?\n",
        "3. What pattern was found?\n",
        "4. Why does it matter?\n",
        "5. What action can be taken?\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 23. Example Insight Statement\n",
        "\n",
        "Instead of saying:\n",
        "\n",
        "> This is a bar chart of Mathematics marks by province.\n",
        "\n",
        "Say:\n",
        "\n",
        "> The chart shows that students from Gauteng have the highest average Mathematics mark. This may suggest differences in preparation, resources, or support needs.\n",
        "\n",
        "Good visualization must lead to interpretation.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 24. Practical Activity\n",
        "\n",
        "Each group must:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Choose one question\n",
        "- Select the correct chart\n",
        "- Explain why the chart is appropriate\n",
        "- Interpret the visual\n",
        "- Present one recommendation\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 25. Mini Challenge\n",
        "\n",
        "A university wants to understand why some students are struggling with Mathematics.\n",
        "\n",
        "Investigate:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Which provinces have the lowest Mathematics performance?\n",
        "- Does attendance affect Mathematics marks?\n",
        "- Does internet access make a difference?\n",
        "- Which campuses have more at-risk students?\n",
        "- What intervention would you recommend?\n",
        "\n",
        "Expected output:\n",
        "\n",
        "- 3 to 5 visualizations\n",
        "- Key insights\n",
        "- Recommendations\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 26. Key Takeaway\n",
        "\n",
        "Data visualization helps us:\n",
        "\n",
        "- See patterns\n",
        "- Understand student behaviour\n",
        "- Identify performance gaps\n",
        "- Detect outliers\n",
        "- Compare groups\n",
        "- Support decision-making\n",
        "- Prepare better machine learning models\n",
        "\n",
        "> Data visualization is not about making charts beautiful. It is about making data understandable and useful.\n"
      ]
    }
